      "content": "In the real world, the government must prioritize immediate crisis management over abstract long-term goals. If the social safety net collapses, the resulting civil unrest and economic chaos will make any debt repayment plan impossible. Therefore, the initial action must be to prevent immediate societal failure, even if it means taking on some temporary debt to stabilize the base. Once the fundamental social and economic structure is stable, then the hard work of fiscal consolidation can begin.",
